---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const title = 'Open_ — Learn to build real things with AI';
const description = 'A free 12-week cohort where you learn to build real products with AI. Not a coding bootcamp. Not prompt engineering. You build and ship something real.';

// TODO: Replace with actual links when ready
const SWORD_FORM_URL = '#';
const DISCORD_URL = '#';
const TWITTER_URL = 'https://x.com/joinopen';
const COHORT_CAP = 100;
---

<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <!-- Skip link for keyboard accessibility -->
  <a href="#main-content" class="sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:absolute focus:top-4 focus:left-4 focus:bg-open-accent focus:text-open-black focus:px-4 focus:py-2 focus:rounded focus:z-[60]">
    Skip to content
  </a>

  <!-- Nav -->
  <nav class="fixed top-0 w-full z-50 bg-open-black/80 backdrop-blur-sm border-b border-white/5">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-4 flex justify-between items-center">
      <a href="#" class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight">Open_</a>
      <a
        href="#sword"
        class="text-sm font-medium text-open-accent hover:text-orange-400 transition-colors"
      >
        Submit Your Sword →
      </a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <main id="main-content" class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="pt-32 pb-20">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight leading-tight mb-6">
        Learn to build real things<br />
        <span class="text-open-accent">with AI.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-open-gray max-w-xl leading-relaxed mb-4">
        I went from a $120k software engineer to making over $200k — plus freelancing
        at $70 an hour. Before that I could only handle my full-time job. What changed?
        I learned how to build with AI. Open_ is a free, 12-week cohort that teaches
        you how to do what I did. Think
        <a href="https://leonnoel.com/100devs/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline hover:text-open-white transition-colors">100Devs</a>,
        but for the AI era.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-open-gray">
        Cohort 1 starts <strong class="text-open-white">Summer 2026</strong>. US only.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Who it's for -->
    <section class="py-16 border-t border-white/5">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-8">Who this is for</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-5">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-open-accent mb-2">Employees</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-open-gray leading-relaxed">You want to build AI tools for your job, automate the boring stuff, or build something on the side that could become your way out.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-5">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-open-accent mb-2">Freelancers</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-open-gray leading-relaxed">You already do client work. You want to add AI-powered tools or services to what you offer — things you couldn't build before.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-5">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-open-accent mb-2">Business owners</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-open-gray leading-relaxed">You've been paying other people to build tools you need. AI makes it possible to build them yourself. This teaches you how.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-5">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-open-accent mb-2">Aspiring founders</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-open-gray leading-relaxed">You have an idea but haven't built it yet. By the end you'll have a shipped product with actual users — not a pitch deck.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Schedule -->
    <section class="py-16 border-t border-white/5">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-8">The schedule</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-open-accent font-mono text-sm mt-0.5 shrink-0 w-8">TUE</span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-open-white">2-hour live session on Twitch</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-open-gray">New concepts, live building, questions welcome.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-open-accent font-mono text-sm mt-0.5 shrink-0 w-8">THU</span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-open-white">2-hour live session on Twitch</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-open-gray">Deeper dives, working on projects together.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-open-accent font-mono text-sm mt-0.5 shrink-0 w-8">SUN</span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-open-white">Office hours</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-open-gray">Bring whatever you're stuck on. Get help from me and the cohort.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-open-accent font-mono text-sm mt-0.5 shrink-0 w-8">24/7</span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-open-white">Discord</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-open-gray">Home base. You'll be assigned to a Crew of 5–6 people. They're your accountability group for the whole program.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 12-week structure -->
    <section class="py-16 border-t border-white/5">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">12 weeks. 3 phases.</h2>
      <p class="text-open-gray text-sm mb-8">10 weeks of content + 2 break weeks built in for catching up and not burning out.</p>
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">
            <span class="text-open-accent font-mono text-sm">Weeks 1–3</span> — Foundations
          </h3>
          <p class="text-open-gray text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Week 1 isn't code — it's how to think. Mental health, scheduling, problem
            decomposition. You learn to break down what you want before you touch any AI tool.
            Week 2 you learn the process: talk through the idea, write a spec, poke holes in it,
            build one piece at a time.
          </p>
          <p class="text-open-gray text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Week 3 is a hackathon. You and your Crew build something together —
            spec it, stress-test it, ship it. Every team presents what they built.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-open-gray text-xs font-mono tracking-wide uppercase">Week 4 — Break</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">
            <span class="text-open-accent font-mono text-sm">Weeks 5–8</span> — Build your own
          </h3>
          <p class="text-open-gray text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Pick something you want to exist. Could be a tool for your job, a side project,
            a business idea — whatever. Spec it, get it reviewed by your Crew, and build.
          </p>
          <p class="text-open-gray text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Week 8 I teach freelancing — not theory, the actual mechanics. My proposal
            template, how I find clients, how I price at $70/hr. You can start freelancing
            before the cohort even ends.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-open-gray text-xs font-mono tracking-wide uppercase">Week 9 — Break</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">
            <span class="text-open-accent font-mono text-sm">Weeks 10–12</span> — Ship it
          </h3>
          <p class="text-open-gray text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Polish, deploy, launch. Week 10 I show you how I used these skills to go from
            $120k to $200k+ at my day job. Week 11 is launch week — everyone ships publicly.
          </p>
          <p class="text-open-gray text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Not everyone will ship by Week 12. That's okay. The cohort ends, but the Discord
            doesn't. The process is yours forever and the community keeps going. You either
            ship during or you ship after — the only way to fail is to stop.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What this is NOT -->
    <section class="py-16 border-t border-white/5">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-8">What this is <span class="text-open-accent">not</span></h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-open-gray">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-open-accent mt-0.5">✕</span>
          <span>Not a coding bootcamp. You don't need to learn programming languages. You need to know how to use an IDE as a text editor.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-open-accent mt-0.5">✕</span>
          <span>Not a prompt engineering course. Learning to "talk to ChatGPT better" isn't what this is.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-open-accent mt-0.5">✕</span>
          <span>Not a get-rich-quick thing. This is 12 weeks of actual work. If you want shortcuts, this isn't it.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-open-accent mt-0.5">✕</span>
          <span>Not passive. You can't just watch the streams and get the value. You have to build.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="py-16 border-t border-white/5">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-8">Questions you probably have</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Do I need to know how to code?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-open-gray leading-relaxed">No. You need to be comfortable using a computer and willing to learn how a text editor works. The whole point of this cohort is that AI does the coding — you learn how to think clearly and direct it.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">How much time per week?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-open-gray leading-relaxed">Plan for about 10 hours. That's 4 hours of live sessions (Tues + Thurs), office hours on Sunday, and daily homework. If you can't do 10, you can still get value — but the people who build the most are the ones who show up consistently.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">What if I can't finish in 12 weeks?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-open-gray leading-relaxed">That's what the break weeks are for — and it's also why the Discord stays open after the cohort ends. You either ship during or you ship after. The process and the community are yours to keep.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Is this really free?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-open-gray leading-relaxed">Yes. No hidden fees, no upsell, no premium tier. 100Devs was free and it changed my life. This is me paying that forward.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Sword -->
    <section id="sword" class="py-16 border-t border-white/5">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The Sword</h2>
      <p class="text-open-gray mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        To apply, you build something first. We call it the Sword.
      </p>
      <p class="text-open-gray mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        It doesn't need to be big or impressive. It needs to be yours. Use any AI tool you want —
        ChatGPT, Claude, Copilot, whatever. Build something: a landing page, a bot, a small tool
        that solves a problem you actually have.
      </p>
      <p class="text-open-gray mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        The point isn't the output. It's the process. We want to see that you tried,
        got stuck, figured things out, and can talk about what happened. Document your build —
        what you asked the AI, what worked, what didn't, what you learned.
      </p>
      <p class="text-open-gray mb-8 leading-relaxed text-sm">
        There's no trick to it. If you put in real effort and can explain what you did,
        you're in. If you paste in a ChatGPT response and call it done, you're not.
      </p>
      <a
        href={SWORD_FORM_URL}
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-open-accent text-open-black font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-orange-400 transition-colors"
      >
        Submit Your Sword →
      </a>
      <p class="text-xs text-open-gray mt-4">
        Cohort 1 is capped at {COHORT_CAP} people. US only for now.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- About Cnid -->
    <section class="py-16 border-t border-white/5">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Who's running this</h2>
      <div class="text-open-gray space-y-4 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          I'm Cnid. Senior software engineer. I already knew how to code, but
          <a href="https://leonnoel.com/100devs/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline hover:text-open-white transition-colors">100Devs</a>
          made me a better engineer. Leon, thank you for everything you've done
          for me and everyone else. Open_ is me trying to pay that forward for the AI era.
        </p>
        <p>
          I've been building with AI since ChatGPT 3.5 dropped. And like most people,
          I started by just throwing ideas at it and seeing what came back. That works for
          small stuff. The second you try to build something real, it falls apart.
        </p>
        <p>
          So I stopped doing that. Now I spend most of my time before I write any code —
          just talking through the idea with AI, writing down what it should actually do,
          poking holes in the plan until it's solid. Then I build it one piece at a time.
          I've shipped a bunch of stuff this way. This site was built this way.
          It's not magic, it's a process. That's what I'm teaching.
        </p>
        <p>
          Why is this free? Because 100Devs was free and it changed everything for me.
          That's it. No upsell, no premium tier, no catch.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer class="py-16 border-t border-white/5">
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 items-start sm:items-center justify-between">
        <div>
          <p class="font-bold text-lg">Open_</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-open-gray mt-1">Free. 12 weeks. Ship something real.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 text-sm">
          <a href={DISCORD_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-open-gray hover:text-open-white transition-colors">
            Discord
          </a>
          <a href={TWITTER_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-open-gray hover:text-open-white transition-colors">
            @joinopen
          </a>
          <a href="#sword" class="text-open-accent hover:text-orange-400 transition-colors">
            Submit Your Sword
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </footer>

  </main>
</Base>
